**Cho Yoon-beom:** So Schumann's future as a pianist was gone in his early 20s. He and his teacher gave up. The teacher had high expectations at first. He even told Schumann's mother, who was paying for lessons, 'Give him a few years under me, and I can make him an incredible pianist.' He was very confident. He had a reason for that confidence. 'Look at my daughter. She's already a child prodigy.' She was 9. He claimed he could make Schumann like her with his teaching method. But since Schumann ended up like that, the teacher focused all his attention on his daughter. Schumann didn't give up on learning piano, but instead, he started a romance.

168
00:23:18,000 --> 00:23:20,000
**Kim Eo-jun:** With whom?

169
00:23:19,000 --> 00:23:22,600
**Cho Yoon-beom:** First with the housekeeper of that house.

170
00:23:25,000 --> 00:23:27,000
**Kim Eo-jun:** He was open-minded.

171
00:23:28,000 --> 00:23:33,200
**Cho Yoon-beom:** After dating the housekeeper, he dated another student of Professor Wieck.

172
00:23:40,000 --> 00:23:45,200
**Kim Eo-jun:** He started with the housekeeper, so all doors were already open.

173
00:23:48,000 --> 00:23:55,200
**Cho Yoon-beom:** He dated around, then went back to the housekeeper. His final destination was the 9-year-old daughter.

174
00:23:57,000 --> 00:23:59,800
**Kim Eo-jun:** That's child abuse, isn't it?

175
00:24:00,000 --> 00:24:03,600
**Cho Yoon-beom:** Years passed and the girl grew up.

176
00:24:03,000 --> 00:24:08,600
**Kim Eo-jun:** When they developed romantic feelings, she must have been 15 or 18.

177
00:24:09,000 --> 00:24:18,600
**Cho Yoon-beom:** Still, there was a big age gap. Nine years. When he first came to the teacher's house, she was just a kid.

178
00:24:14,000 --> 00:24:19,600
**Kim Eo-jun:** The age gap isn't much once they're older, but 10s and 20s...

179
00:24:18,000 --> 00:24:27,600
**Cho Yoon-beom:** Her name was Clara Wieck. She later became Clara Schumann. The famous Clara Schumann who appeared in our Brahms and Mendelssohn lectures.

180
00:24:29,000 --> 00:24:33,400
**Kim Eo-jun:** She lived her life as a pianist after that.

181
00:24:32,000 --> 00:24:36,800
**Cho Yoon-beom:** Since she was the teacher's daughter, the teacher wouldn't approve.

182
00:24:38,000 --> 00:24:46,800
**Kim Eo-jun:** Especially when he's a Greco-Roman wrestler and his future as a pianist is bleak. I wouldn't give him my daughter.

183
00:24:44,000 --> 00:25:02,000
**Cho Yoon-beom:** He opposed it vehemently. It was no joke. He even set up legal measures. If she married Schumann, she wouldn't inherit anything. But Professor Wieck's opposition had a benefit. He blocked all men approaching Clara. The competitors disappeared. Schumann just had to succeed.

184
00:25:12,000 --> 00:25:24,800
**Kim Eo-jun:** Not everything goes as planned in the world. Especially relationships. He cleared the path, and Schumann just had to walk it. The problem was his remaining path—his major was law.

185
00:25:32,000 --> 00:25:36,800
**Kim Eo-jun:** Who knows what will happen. He hated law so much.

186
00:25:39,000 --> 00:25:51,000
**Cho Yoon-beom:** Law was what he hated most, but he turned out to be a legal expert. He thought he could attack his future father-in-law with law. He sued him.

187
00:25:47,000 --> 00:25:53,400
**Kim Eo-jun:** Sued his father-in-law? For blocking the marriage? To allow him to marry her legally?

188
00:25:55,000 --> 00:25:57,000
**Cho Yoon-beom:** He sued him.

