193
00:26:43,000 --> 00:26:48,200
**Cho Yoon-beom:** If the frontal lobe is damaged, don't you get angry easily?

194
00:26:47,000 --> 00:26:51,000
**Kim Ka-ram:** Yes, and autonomic nervous system control becomes difficult.

195
00:26:49,000 --> 00:27:40,200
**Kim Eo-jun:** You forget what you just said. Yesterday was Armed Forces Day. At the ceremony, the President received a salute and had to give the 'At ease' command. He forgot it. 'Unit, at ease.' He should have done it so the commander could command the whole unit. Otherwise, they have to stay at attention. But he forgot and just blinked. He receiving the salute and then should say 'at ease'. How could he forget that? Looking at Schumann, it must be the alcohol. I'm sure they told him. It's just one step. One. 'Unit, at ease'. Maybe if there were three steps... but just one! Anyway, back to Schumann. He got away with it through law. He claimed there was no evidence of him drinking too much.

196
00:27:57,000 --> 00:27:59,000
**Cho Yoon-beom:** Lack of evidence.

197
00:28:02,000 --> 00:28:09,600
**Kim Eo-jun:** There's evidence here, video of what he said! I didn't say it! Back to Schumann. He sued.

198
00:28:18,000 --> 00:28:28,400
**Cho Yoon-beom:** He escaped the alcohol issue through lack of evidence. Then the professor mentioned schizophrenia. 'He used two strange names when writing before. He fluctuates.'

199
00:28:30,000 --> 00:28:32,000
**Kim Eo-jun:** Multiple personalities.

200
00:28:32,000 --> 00:28:44,800
**Cho Yoon-beom:** And that he has no future. Because of his broken finger, he wouldn't earn much money. 'If you want my daughter, you must earn at least this much per month.'

201
00:28:43,000 --> 00:28:47,800
**Kim Eo-jun:** A father could say that. But there's no legal basis.

202
00:28:47,000 --> 00:28:56,200
**Cho Yoon-beom:** Eventually, he won the trial and got married, but those words always stayed in his mind. He always thought about it.

203
00:28:54,000 --> 00:28:56,800
**Kim Eo-jun:** What did the daughter see?

204
00:28:56,000 --> 00:29:02,400
**Cho Yoon-beom:** She saw him since she was a kid. Taking lessons in the same house.

205
00:29:00,000 --> 00:29:06,800
**Kim Eo-jun:** All other men were blocked by her father, and she only saw this guy dating.

206
00:29:07,000 --> 00:29:18,600
**Cho Yoon-beom:** And when there's so much opposition, doesn't it create a stubbornness? He's even suing for our love. How much must he love me to go to court?

207
00:29:19,000 --> 00:29:25,800
**Cho Yoon-beom:** Clara was actually in a difficult position in the middle. He was suing her father.

208
00:29:25,000 --> 00:29:39,400
**Kim Eo-jun:** No, girls that age aren't in a difficult position. They are moved by the burning love for them, more than their father. Would she have married him if she were in a difficult position?

209
00:29:37,000 --> 00:29:44,600
**Cho Yoon-beom:** She was a kid who traveled abroad and performed, but her father was always next to her.

210
00:29:44,000 --> 00:29:48,000
**Kim Eo-jun:** She must have wanted to escape her father.

211
00:29:48,000 --> 00:29:59,600
**Kim Eo-jun:** She could marry him because of that special situation. The father strictly protected and blocked everything, but the Greco-Roman wrestler broke through. She might have been moved.

212
00:30:03,000 --> 00:30:07,400
**Cho Yoon-beom:** Someone helped Schumann win this trial. Professor Wieck's ex-wife.

213
00:30:12,000 --> 00:30:17,200
**Kim Eo-jun:** 'My husband was always like that.' Sounds like a soap opera.

214
00:30:17,000 --> 00:30:23,400
**Cho Yoon-beom:** So when they got married, the father didn't come, but the biological mother did.

215
00:30:23,000 --> 00:30:29,400
**Kim Eo-jun:** So Schumann had a side that appealed to women. The mother-in-law took his side.

216
00:30:33,000 --> 00:30:44,600
**Cho Yoon-beom:** Most of his acquaintances were on his side. Their social circles overlapped in the music world, and most supported him. Professor Wieck's personality had some issues too.

217
00:30:43,000 --> 00:30:51,400
**Kim Eo-jun:** He must have had a lovable side. Or triggered protective instincts. Okay, I understand Schumann. So he married Clara.

218
00:30:53,000 --> 00:31:01,800
**Cho Yoon-beom:** After marrying Clara, he simultaneously tried to prove he was a proper person. He tried to get a doctoral degree.

219
00:31:07,000 --> 00:31:13,400
**Kim Eo-jun:** Getting a doctoral degree... Why does it feel so automatic these days? Doctoral degree.

220
00:31:14,000 --> 00:31:21,200
**Cho Yoon-beom:** And he started a magazine. At that time, he wasn't known as a composer or pianist.

221
00:31:21,000 --> 00:31:23,000
**Kim Eo-jun:** A critic?

222
00:31:22,000 --> 00:31:30,400
**Cho Yoon-beom:** He was known as a critic and editor-in-chief of a music magazine. Neue Zeitschrift für Musik. It still exists.

223
00:31:29,000 --> 00:31:39,400
**Kim Eo-jun:** Since he could perform and had musical talent, plus writing skills... He could perform and was a great music critic. He had a standing.

224
00:31:40,000 --> 00:31:54,800
**Cho Yoon-beom:** He saw a performer named Chopin and was amazed, so he wrote a review. He submitted it to another magazine, but the exaggeration was too much. The review was too literary. Like 'God has descended'.

225
00:31:56,000 --> 00:31:59,200
**Kim Eo-jun:** He was being over the top.

226
00:31:58,000 --> 00:32:02,000
**Kim Eo-jun:** I know what kind of person he was.

227
00:32:01,000 --> 00:32:13,400
**Cho Yoon-beom:** For such people, there's a solution. Make your own magazine. If nobody accepts your writing. So he made one. He started making a name for himself as an editor-in-chief.

228
00:32:10,000 --> 00:32:13,200
**Kim Eo-jun:** Now, let's hear 'Echo of Troy'.

229
00:32:13,000 --> 00:32:17,800
**Cho Yoon-beom:** Träumerei. It's a collection of small piano pieces called Kinderszenen.

230
00:32:20,000 --> 00:32:22,000
**Kim Eo-jun:** Why childhood?

231
00:32:21,000 --> 00:32:37,400
**Cho Yoon-beom:** He wanted to express childhood scenes. While he was writing this, Clara said, 'I'm under 9 years old, do you see me as a child?' He expressed childhood sensitivity, and just hearing it makes you feel it's truly pure.

232
00:32:35,000 --> 00:32:41,400
**Kim Eo-jun:** Childhood sensitivity... I'll listen and decide with my sensitivity. Small dream, the famous Träumerei.

